alt: Photo by The Jojoba Company on October 29, 2024. May be an image of hair product, hand cream and text.
caption:
Did you know our Australian Jojoba is suitable for all skin types?

➡️ Dry Skin: Jojoba will bring long-lasting hydration to your skin and keep flakiness/scaliness at bay.

➡️ Oily Skin: Jojoba will provide the hydration that oily skin needs and in turn, will help to rebalance the production of oil in your skin.

➡️ Sensitive Skin: Jojoba will hydrate your skin and calm any irritation.

➡️ Blemish Prone Skin: Jojoba will help to calm breakouts and rebalance oil production.

➡️ Combination Skin: Jojoba will help hydrate where your skin is dry and rebalance oil where it is more oily, like the T-zone.

What's in my bag? Just my must-have Australian Jojoba! 👜✨

Perfect for on-the-go hydration, it keeps skin moisturised and glowing wherever and whenever. Whether it's running errands or heading out for a night, this little gem is a go-to for instant, long-lasting moisture 💧

alt: Photo by The Jojoba Company on October 30, 2024. May be an image of 1 person and text.
caption:
There's no better feeling than hopping into bed after you've lathered your face with Ultimate Youth Potion 🤩 

Who else loves the calming scent of linden blossom? 🙋‍♀️

Revealing the secret to radiant skin ✨ 
Peek inside and discover the brightening and hydrating power of our Vitamin C Glow Potion!

Did you know that the collagen in our skin starts to decline around 25 years of age and then 1-2% every year after that? 

Get a head start on replenishing the collagen in your skin with our hero hyaluronic acid serum, Ultimate Serum ❄️💦 

Not only is this viral serum made with the first vegan human-identical collagen, HumaColl2®, but it has been scientifically proven to outperform retinol in the production of collagen!*

*HumaColl21™ stimulates collagen type 1 by 197% vs 117% for Retinol when tested in an invitro control group.

alt: Photo by The Jojoba Company on October 30, 2024. Puede ser una imagen de 1 persona, producto para el pelo y texto.
caption:
We often get asked: Why apply Jojoba before moisturiser when it is recommended to apply oils after moisturiser? 🤔

💡 The answer? Jojoba is unlike any other oil.

Oils are usually applied AFTER moisturiser to seal in moisture and act as a protective barrier. But, rather than sitting on top of the skin like most oils do, Jojoba travels deeper down into the skin's layers. This is because it mimics the structure of the oils in our skin. 

To ensure our skin reaps the full benefits of our Jojoba and facial oils, applying them first ensures they are absorbed first and will therefore be more effective!

The high antioxidant content will help fight free radicals (which contribute to ageing) from UV rays and pollution as you go about your day.

caption:
Ever wondered where the magic of our Australian Jojoba comes from? It all starts right here on our family-owned farm in Yenda, NSW 🌾

From seed to bottle, we oversee every step of the process, ensuring you get the purest, most potent Australian Jojoba possible. We're passionate about sustainable farming practices that nurture the land and produce the highest quality Wadi-Wadi Jojoba 🌱

#SmarterNaturalSkincare #BringJojobaBack

Although it is referred to as an oil, Jojoba is a wax ester 🌱✨

Our sebum is made up of three parts: wax esters, triglycerides and squalene. 

While you can find multiple plant sources of triglycerides and squalene, Jojoba is the ONLY known plant source of wax esters, so it's the only product you need for replenishing the wax esters in your skin! 

It's 100% pure and healthy for your skin, giving you the vital nutrients and antioxidants you need to glow 💛

What is blue light damage? 💻📺📱

Blue light is everywhere, with the sun being the biggest source. However, electronic devices like phones, laptops, and TVs also emit significant amounts. 

Some research suggests exposing your skin to blue light may contribute to premature ageing. This includes increased fine lines, wrinkles, uneven skin tone and hyperpigmentation.

Ectoin, an ingredient in our Illuminating Tinted Moisturiser with SPF15, helps shield against blue light damage by reducing free radicals, stabilising cell membranes, and keeping skin hydrated.

caption:
What does 'incidental sun exposure' mean?

Our NEW Illuminating Tinted Moisturiser features SPF15, which shields the skin from incidental sun exposure to UVA/UVB rays. 

Incidental sun exposure refers to the ultraviolet (UV) radiation you get from the sun throughout the day, often without even realising it. It's the sun you encounter during everyday activities. Here are some examples:

☀️ Walking to work or running errands
☀️ Waiting at a bus stop
☀️ Driving in a car
☀️ Sitting by a window at home or work

Even if you don't get much exposure to the sun, you can feel good knowing the Illuminating Tinted Moisturiser SPF15 is taking care of your skin.

caption:
So what is Ectoin and why is it great for your skin?

Ectoin is a superhero for stressed-out skin! It's a natural ingredient found in extremophiles (organisms that thrive in harsh environments) that acts like a shield. 

🤍 Reduces redness and irritation: 
Ectoin calms and soothes the skin, making it ideal for sensitive complexions.

🤍 Boosts hydration: 
It helps your skin retain moisture, keeping it plump and healthy.

🤍 Protects from environmental damage: 
Ectoin acts as a barrier against aggressors like pollution and blue light from electronics, which can damage your skin over time.
